    • Method Detail

      • getBT

        public jbt.model.core.ModelTask getBT​(java.lang.String name)
        Returns a behaviour tree by its name, or null in case it cannot be found. It must be noted that the trees that are retrieved belong to the class, not to the instance (that is, the trees are static members of the class), so they are shared among all the instances of this class.
        Specified by:
        getBT in interface jbt.execution.core.IBTLibrary

      • iterator

        public java.util.Iterator<jbt.util.Pair<java.lang.String,jbt.model.core.ModelTask>> iterator()
        Returns an Iterator that is able to iterate through all the elements in the library. It must be noted that the iterator does not support the "remove()" operation. It must be noted that the trees that are retrieved belong to the class, not to the instance (that is, the trees are static members of the class), so they are shared among all the instances of this class.
        Specified by:
        iterator in interface java.lang.Iterable<jbt.util.Pair<java.lang.String,jbt.model.core.ModelTask>>
